title: Fear Itself - 1969
description:
Fear Itself was a short-lived psychedelic blues-rock band formed by Ellen McIlwaine in the late 1960&#039;s in Atlanta, Georgia. The band featured McIlwaine singing lead vocals as well as performing harp, rhythm guitar and organ. 

Inspired by Jimi Hendrix and Cream, the group&#039;s sound was unique due in large part to the McIlwaine&#039;s gospel-bluesy voice and lyrics.
